description:
Year: 2007, Piazza S. Marco, Venice, Italy
Genre:  Concert Live, Instrumental
Director: Giovanni Morricone
Starring: Ennio Morricone, Susana Rigacci, Roma Sinfonietta Orchestra, Choir La Fenice.




This is blu-ray of Ennio Morricone Conducting his own music in Peace Notes, a 9/11 Peace Concert - Live In Venice with the Roma Sinfonietta Orchestra, Choir La Fenice, Soprano Susanna Rigacci performed on 9/10 and 9/11 2007. Filmed in high definition, featuring many of Morricone's best loved film scores. Morricone is traveling around the world performing this amazing concert for peace, which was conducted in front of the United Nations, portions of which can be seen on this blu-ray.

Arguably one of cinemaÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢s greatest composers, Ennio Morricone has built a legacy of passionate, emotive and sublime recordings to accompany some of international cinemas most iconic films. He remains a celebrated and at times controversial, figure within classical and film music, having released numerous best-selling albums and being honoured with a special Academy Award in 2007 for ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œhis magnificent and multifaceted contributions to the art of film music.ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚ï¿½
Now, from his impressive back catalogue as a cinematic composer, the illustrious Ennio Morricone conducts a moving and uplifting tribute to the victims of the 9/11 attacks and to all victims of unjust tragedies throughout history.
Filmed on September 10, 2007 in high definition at the historic Piazza San Marco, Venice this remarkable live performance features music from Cinema Paradiso, The Good The Bad and The Ugly, Once Upon a Time in America, Love Circle, The Mission and many other timeless classics.


